}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "0207B", "ROHS", and a date code of '''1209''' (presumably Mar. 2012) is silkscreened on the board of a production unit <small>([[User:M86|M86]]'s unit)</small>. :Two '''Skyworks''' / '''SiGe''' SE2595L FEMs are used. There is no RF shielding.
This device appears to be a [[Zioncom WL0207]]. :W6RRNX-N600UBE is the FCC ID on the label, but is not applicable to this version of the device.
This device has an alternative model of RNWD-11008.
''' A newer revision of the device has been released (late 2013) using RT5572.''' :W6RRNX-N600UBE passed through the FCC on 03/19/2013. The photos and manual show the device with RT5572.
